  "prompt": "Is it a symptom of OCD to repeat words? (Repetitive, words and speech)",
  "response": "Yes, repeating words or phrases can be a symptom of Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD). OCD is characterized by obsessive thoughts and compulsive behaviors. In some cases, individuals with OCD may engage in repetitive speech patterns as part of their compulsions. They might feel an uncontrollable urge to say certain words or phrases repeatedly to alleviate anxiety or prevent a feared outcome. However, repetitive speech can also be associated with other conditions, such as Tourette Syndrome or anxiety disorders, so it's important to consult a mental health professional for an accurate diagnosis and appropriate treatment.",
